ructive and post-ischemic kidney fibrosis. Kidney Int 80:1170–1181.\n\n15. Wang S, Denichilo M, Brubaker C, Hirschberg R (2001) Connective tissue growth\nfactor in tubulointerstitial injury of diabetic nephropathy. Kidney Int 60(1):96–105.\n\n16. ten Berge D, et al. (2011) Embryonic stem cells require Wnt proteins to prevent dif-\nferentiation to epiblast stem cells. Nat Cell Biol 13(9):1070–1075.\n\n17. Sieczkiewicz GJ, Herman IM (2003) TGF-beta 1 signaling controls retinal pericyte\ncontractile protein expression. Microvasc Res 66(3):190–196.\n\n18. Hall-Glenn F, et al. (2012) CCN2/CTGF is essential for pericyte adhesion and endo-\nthelial basement membrane formation during angiogenesis. PLoS ONE 7:e30562.\n\n19. Kawata K, et al. (2012) Role of low-density lipoprotein receptor related protein\n1 (LRP1) in CCN2 protein transport in chondrocytes. J Cell Sci 125:2965–2972.\n\n20. Walker N, et al. (2011) Resident tissue-specific mesenchymal progenitor cells con-\ntribute to fibrogenesis in human lung allografts. Am J Pathol 178(6):2461–2469.\n\n21. Leask A (2008) Targeting the TGFbeta, endothelin-1 and CCN2 axis to combat fibrosis\nin scleroderma. Cell Signal 20(8):1409–1414.\n\n22. Kokubu C, et al. (2004) Skeletal defects in ringelschwanz mutant mice reveal that\nLrp6 is required for proper somitogenesis and osteogenesis. Development 131(21):\n5469–5480.\n\nRen et al. PNAS | January 22, 2013 | vol. 110 | no. 4 | 1445\n\nM\nED\n\nIC\nA\nL\nSC\n\nIE\nN\nC\nES\n\nView publication statsView publication stats\n\nhttp://www.pnas.org/lookup/suppl/doi:10.1073/pnas.1211179110/-/DCSupplemental/pnas.201211179SI.pdf?targetid=nameddest=SF7\nhttp://www.pnas.org/lookup/suppl/doi:10.1073/pnas.1211179110/-/DCSupplemental/pnas.201211179SI.pdf?targetid=nameddest=SF8\nhttp://www.pnas.org/lookup/suppl/doi:10.1073/pnas.1211179110/-/DCSupplemental/pnas.201211179SI.pdf?targetid=nameddest=SF8\nhttps://www.researchgate.net/publication/234098410\n\n"}